The code in this project is made available under the MIT License.
It is based on voxelia by André Kiste, available at https://gitlab.com/bergice/voxelia/-/tree/master
Changing the code is permitted by the MIT license and modifications do not need to be made public or
released as source code.

The assets it uses are mostly not covered by the MIT License (as they are not software), and have their own
creators and license terms.

The character and environment graphics use art by Gustavo Vituri, https://gvituri.itch.io/isometric-trpg
The license says 'You are free to use all sprites in both personal and commercial projects.'
and to credit Gustavo Vituri. Usage in NFTs is not permitted. See assets/isometric-trpg-License.txt

Contains a scene2d.ui skin by Raymond Buckley, https://ray3k.wordpress.com/clean-crispy-ui-skin-for-libgdx/
License is CC-BY 4.0, so it requires attribution to Raymond Buckley. See assets/Skin-License.txt

Contains a song by Komiku, 'Road 4 Fight', https://freemusicarchive.org/music/Komiku/Helice_Awesome_Dance_Adventure_/road-4-fight/
It is licensed under Creative Commons 0, releasing it into the public domain, and as such does not require attribution.
See 'assets/Komiku - Road 4 Fight - License.txt'

The font present in the assets is Cozette, by ines, https://github.com/the-moonwitch/Cozette
It is MIT-licensed. See assets/Cozette-License.txt , which uses an earlier copyright status

